                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d817">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SPA1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stovall</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-06">
                        <hi rend="italic">November 6, 1914</hi>.</date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>50. Your November 5, 10 a.m. The Department regrets that it can do nothing in
                    this case, as commercial cables are censored by belligerents and not by American
                    authorities. This seems to be a matter that should be taken up by the Swiss
                    ministers in London and Paris and not by this Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
